Police Minister, General Bheki Cele, and KwaZulu-Natal Provincial Commissioner, Lt General Nhlanhla Mkhwanazi, and his management team alongside Community Safety MEC, Peggy Nkonyeni, conducted inspections of police operations that have been put in place to minimise crime and criminal acts during the holiday season at the South Coast beaches on 1 January.  These site visits saw police top brass interact with shoppers, holidaymakers and residents, on their experiences of crossing over to the new year, as they embarked on a walkthrough at places of business and leisure. Following three weeks of inspections of operations by the South African Police Service in all nine provinces, as part of the Safer Festive Season Inspection Tour undertaken by the Police Ministry and the SAPS top management in all nine provinces. The police top brass also interacted with shoppers, holidaymakers, motorists and residents, on their experiences of the New Yearâ€™s celebrations and engaged them on some of their safety concerns as they embark on a walkthrough at places of business and leisure. The last stop for the Safer Festive Season Inspection Tour ended off at the popular Durban beachfront, which attracts visitors and bathers from far and wide on the first day of the new year.